title: Grateful Dead Live at Giants Stadium on 1993-06-06
lineage: 1st gen Maxell XLIIS > Nakamichi DR-2 > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab > R8Brain > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 1644 Tagged
description:
Set 1

Here Comes Sunshine, Minglewood Blues, Ramble On Rose, Broken Arrow, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Lazy River Road, Let It Grow

Set 2

Bertha-> Good Lovin'-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Jam-> Corinna-> Attics Of My Life-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Liberty

Sting opened

reviews.review_text: Swirly Thanx Andrew.  Decent sounding aud.  There seems to be a swirling type of dropout on one channel from time to time.  Some yahoo gets off on imitating Jerry during Throwing.  Great setlist and worth a listen.  I am opening my radio show this week with Space thru NFA.  Peace

Weak Show in Person Had upper deck tickets.  It was a hot day.  The sound quality was terrible.  I love Here Comes Sunshine.  But when the show started I wasn't even sure if it was the band or "house music."

Didn't help that the girl I went to with was my ex.  When I picked her up I had to witness her kissing her new boyfriend.  Didn't even know she has one.  Giants Stadium shows never seemed to hit it off in the later years except for the Eyes Opener a couple years earlier.

I am downloading this.  Out of my 63 shows I saw, this is the last one for me to find.  So now I have every Dead show I ever saw!
